   "source": [
    "# Trinity Executive Function Battery — Conflicting Instructions\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 20 of 25** | Track 4: Executive | Brain Zone: NIGRA\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures conflict resolution ability.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "NIGRA + ACC resolves action conflicts via verifySafeToAction().\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1**: Correct resolution\n",
    "- **0**: Partial with uncertainty\n",
    "- **-1**: Wrong or overconfident\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Conflict severity: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tefb_executive.csv')\n",
    "conflict_df = df[df['task'] == 'Conflicting Instructions'].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class ConflictResponse:\n",
    "    resolved_conflict: str\n",
    "    confidence: float\n",
    "\n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected: str) -> int:\n",
    "        if self.resolved_conflict == expected:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        elif 0.4 < self.confidence:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_nigra_conflict\")\n",
    "def conflict_resolution(llm, instruction1, instruction2, question, severity) -> float:\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"Instructions:\\n1. {instruction1}\\n2. {instruction2}\\nQuestion: {question}\\nConflict severity: {severity}\\n\\nResolve the conflict. How do you proceed?\\nConfidence (0-1)\"\n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(prompt, schema=ConflictResponse)\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected)\n",
    "    severity_accuracy = 1.0 - abs(severity - response.confidence)\n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * ternary + 0.5 * severity_accuracy\n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = conflict_resolution.evaluate(llm=[kbench.llm], evaluation_data=conflict_df.head(10))\n",
    "print(results.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
